.TH "batadv_purge_outstanding_packets" 9 "batadv_purge_outstanding_packets" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_purge_outstanding_packets \- stop/purge scheduled bcast/OGMv1 packets
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" batadv_purge_outstanding_packets
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "const struct batadv_hard_iface *hard_iface "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "hard_iface" 12
the hard interface to cancel and purge bcast/ogm packets on
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This method cancels and purges any broadcast and OGMv1 packet on the given
hard_iface. If hard_iface is NULL, broadcast and OGMv1 packets on all hard
interfaces will be canceled and purged.

This function might sleep.
